 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub78.ezboard.com/uaakla2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>aakla2</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=ttp://www.geocities.com/aakla2/EQ000014.jpg BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/18/01 1:10:49 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: but </span><hr size=1> well here are some numbers if you raise your ac from 1000 to 1100 you will take like 17% less damage against a 55lvl mob now if you raise your ac from 1100 to 1200 you will take like 2-4% less damage against a lvl 55 mob. its just like if you go and fight a 20th lvl mob your ac will only help you out to a certain point before any miore ac is not effective. or something liek that. so after you get 1100ac you start looking for hp/stm items if you can get 7hp for every 1 ac you loose then its a good trade of (the 7 to 1 ratio is thoggs formula) got to give credit where credit is due. other high lvl warriors have agreed that this is a good ratio to follow. now if you fight a lvl 60+ mob then in theory ac over 1100 will help. but whenyou get to that point you will have like 24-36 people with you and you will be sharing damage so it wont matter much unless everyone there has like 1200+ac and also thosemobs hit for like 500 so that little extra ac wont matter unless its alot of extra ac, or something like that <p><p> <img src="http://www.geocities.com/aakla2/EQ000014.jpg"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub78.ezboard.com/uganzo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ganzo</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://people.mw.mediaone.net/aminevich/images/smurf.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/con's RED</span><br>  Posts: 387<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/18/0